<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-24T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.Consultation(2)/414: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-24T20:00:00-04:00">July 24, 1940—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. For White from the Secretary of the Treasury. Reference your 9, July
                            23, 6 p.m. I am willing to go along provided the Government and Central
                            Bank of each particular country would guarantee individually and
                            collectively the gold loan. [Morgenthau.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>